messages:
Name: Felipe Caicedo
Nationality: Ecuador
Date of Birth: September 5, 1988
Position: Attacker
Current club: Internazionale
Serie A clubs played for: Lazio, Genoa, Internazionale

Felipe Caicedo is an Internazionale attacker who has made 12 appearances in this season's Serie A, with three of these coming for his current club. He had previously played for Genoa in the competition during 2021/2022.

The last league match that Caicedo played came on May 22 for Internazionale against Sampdoria; a game that he played 17 minutes in during a 3-0 win. In total, he has notched one Serie A goal in 2021/2022, and provided two assists. He has been booked once.
His opening goal of the campaign came in the 3-2 loss against Torino on October 22.
In last season's Serie A, Caicedo featured in 25 games for Lazio and scored eight goals.

Caicedo moved to Internazionale on loan in January 2022 from Genoa, for whom he has made nine league appearances in total, scoring one goal and providing two assists, after joining the club in August 2021 from Lazio.

It was on August 20, 2017 that Caicedo made his Serie A debut during his spell at Lazio, at the age of 28 years and 349 days, against SPAL. He first appeared in a Serie A fixture for current team Internazionale in his side's game versus Genoa on February 25, 2022.

So far in his Serie A career, he has played 117 matches in the competition, with 29 goals and seven assists. Caicedo is yet to be shown a red card in the competition, despite playing 117 games so far, with 18 yellow cards collected overall.
